# Security response headers.
#
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT — where this file does and does not take effect:
#   • Cloudflare Pages / Netlify  → applied automatically. Nothing else to do.
#   • GitHub Pages (this project's default host) → IGNORED. GitHub Pages does
#     not read _headers files. To get these headers on GitHub Pages, front the
#     site with Cloudflare (proxied DNS) and add a "Response Header Transform"
#     rule, or move hosting to Cloudflare Pages. Paste the same values below.
#
# CSP notes: 'unsafe-inline' is required for scripts because next-themes injects
# an inline anti-FOUC theme script and the JSON-LD <script> tags are inline, and
# a statically-exported site cannot mint a per-request nonce. It is required for
# styles because Tailwind and motion emit inline styles. The remaining
# directives still meaningfully shrink the attack surface (no plugins, no
# framing, no <base> hijack, no cross-origin form posts).

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(self), camera=(), microphone=(), payment=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' https: data:; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; object-src 'none'
